Change-Id: I77f57d659555d12f510132be8b4831dbbc678ca5","distinct":false,"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/tensorflow/tensorflow/commits/6dec10805924a5a9ef6babe8809f796dc8c262f4"},{"sha":"ed84f7611a9629657dbf5073c8b50a42e48337a7","author":{"email":"5bcb0c34b484f21048fb46d802116fb172e4e0a2@google.com","name":"Frederik Gossen"},"message":"[ShapeAnalysis] Eliminate more redundant shape constraints in real-world cases

Eliminate more redundant `cstr_reshapable` constraints. Collect all the factors
before comparing the number of elements and the dynamic shape for compatibility.
Previously, we did this only for the symbolic expression that falls out of the
`num_elements` op, not for the individual dimensions of the dynamic shape. With
this, we are able to eliminate the `cstr_reshapable` in the real-world
integration test.
